title: [JIT] Unsupported op descriptor masked_fill
body_html:
Don't support masked_fill in dispatch. Example failure:

======================================================================
ERROR: test_masked_fill (__main__.TestAutogradGenerated)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "test/test_autograd.py", line 3665, in do_test
    check(name)
  File "test/test_autograd.py", line 3587, in check
    check_against_reference(self, create_traced_fn(fn), fn, (self_variable,) + args_variable)
  File "test/test_autograd.py", line 3498, in check_against_reference
    outputs_test = func(*nograd_inputs)
  File "test/test_autograd.py", line 3446, in traced_fn
    return traced(*inputs_tensors)
RuntimeError: Unsupported op descriptor: masked_fill-2-value_t. File a bug report.

Affected tests:

  • test_masked_fill
  • test_masked_fill_broadcast_rhs
  • test_masked_fill_scalar
  • test_masked_fill_scalar_broadcast_rhs
  • test_masked_fill_scalar_variable
  • test_masked_fill_tensor

body:
Don't support `masked_fill` in dispatch. Example failure:

```
======================================================================
ERROR: test_masked_fill (__main__.TestAutogradGenerated)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "test/test_autograd.py", line 3665, in do_test
    check(name)
  File "test/test_autograd.py", line 3587, in check
    check_against_reference(self, create_traced_fn(fn), fn, (self_variable,) + args_variable)
  File "test/test_autograd.py", line 3498, in check_against_reference
    outputs_test = func(*nograd_inputs)
  File "test/test_autograd.py", line 3446, in traced_fn
    return traced(*inputs_tensors)
RuntimeError: Unsupported op descriptor: masked_fill-2-value_t. File a bug report.
```

Affected tests:
- `test_masked_fill`
- `test_masked_fill_broadcast_rhs`
- `test_masked_fill_scalar`
- `test_masked_fill_scalar_broadcast_rhs`
- `test_masked_fill_scalar_variable`
- `test_masked_fill_tensor`
